narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: An in depth look at the writings and times of Niccolo Machiavelli. Touches on everything from The Prince, The Discourses, Florentine Histories to Guicciardini, just to name a few. Midterm paper and final paper in classic seminar style. I would absolutely recommend this course to a fellow student.

I would absolutely recommend this class! Professor Ardito is a fabulous professor, and her knowledge of Machiavelli is just incredible. The level of preparation that went into each section was really wonderful. I would also highly recommend going to her office hours and just talking with her. It was at office hours that I learned the most.
I would recommend this course. Machiavelli is constantly referenced in our culture, but few know anything other than he must be tricky or something, this course will go well beyond that.
